 https://www.nick.com/shows/crashletes\n}}\n\n'''''Crashletes''''' is an American [[sports]] television program that premiered on [[Nickelodeon]] on July 5, 2016. The program is hosted by [[Brandon Broady]] and Stevie Nelson. Retired American football player [[Rob Gronkowski]] was the main host for the first two seasons but left the show in the third.\n\n== Premise ==\nBrandon and Stevie, along with a guest host from the world of sports (e.g. basketball player [[DeAndre Jordan]], snowboarder [[Shaun White]], Olympic gymnast [[Laurie Hernandez]], etc.) and an audience of kids, react to various viral videos of people failing at sports, which they call \"crashletes.\" Each clip is shown in a package of about four to seven clips, and a recurring segment is the Crashdown (formerly known as the Gronkdown when [[Rob Gronkowski|Gronkowski]] was host), where a top 5 list of clips under a certain theming is shown.\n\n== Production ==\n''Crashletes'' was renewed for a second season on September 1, 2016, and the second season premiered on September 16, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/crashletes-season-two-renewal-nickelodeon-sports-series/|title=Crashletes: Season Two Renewal for Nickelodeon Sports Series|work=TV Series Finale|author=Cindy McLennan|date=September 1, 2016|access-date=October 7, 2016}}</ref> Following a silent renewal, the third season's premiere on [[TeenNick]] was announced to be on February 11, 2018,<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2018/01/16/nickelodeons-viral-sports-clip-series-crashletes-returns-for-an-epic-third-season-premiering-sunday-feb-11-at-10-am-et-pt-in-teennicks-nicksports-block-218214/20180116nickelodeon01/|title=Nickelodeon's Viral Sports Clip Series \"Crashletes\" Returns for an Epic Third Season, Premiering Sunday, Feb. 11, at 10 A.M. (ET/PT) in TeenNick's NickSports Block|publisher=Nickelodeon|via=The Futon Critic|date=January 16, 2018|access-date=February 9, 2018}}</ref> but new episodes did not air in February 2018. On January 25, 2019, it was announced that the third season would premiere on February 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/01/25/nickelodeon-premiering-new-seasons-of-crashletes-and-the-dude-perfect-show-in-february-600414/20190125nickelodeon01/|title=Nickelodeon Premiering New Seasons of ''Crashletes'' and ''The Dude Perfect Show'' in February|publisher=Nickelodeon|via=The Futon Critic|date=January 25, 2019|access-date=January 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n\n=== Series overview ===\n<!-- full linking is used in the following template because it is transcluded to the main series article -->\n\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n\n| color1    = #87CEFA\n| link1     = <includeonly>List of Crashletes episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2016)\n| episodes1 = 19\n| start1    = {{Start date|2016|7|5}}\n| end1      = {{End date|2016|9|9}}\n\n| color2    = #FFD700\n| link2     = <includeonly>List of Crashletes episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2016\u201317)\n| episodes2 = 21\n| start2    = {{Start date|2016|9|16}}\n| end2      = {{End date|2017|4|23}}\n\n| color3    = #F46D25\n| link3     = <includeonly>List of Crashletes episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2019)\n| episodes3 = <!-- displays TBA if empty; requires a reference if filled in -->\n| start3    = {{Start date|2019|2|3}}\n| end3      = <!-- displays TBA if empty; requires a reference if filled in -->\n\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n=== Season 1 (2016) ===\n{{Episode table\n| background      = #87CEFA\n| overall         = \n| season          = \n| title           = \n| titleR          = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it Season 1\" />\n| airdate         = \n| airdateR        = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it Season 1\" />\n| prodcode        = \n| prodcodeR       = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" />\n| viewers         = \n| country         = U.S.\n| episodes        = \n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Episode