o he is taken to the home of Sir George Woodley ([[John Harvey (actor)|John Harvey]]), where an Italian doctor, Benvolio ([[Henry Vidon]]), is visiting. Betrayed the doctor and Little John are arrested. Robin and Tuck's rescue attempt succeeds in rescuing the doctors but not Little John. The Sheriff is badly wounded by Robin Hood and a bargain is made by the doctor to save both Little John and the Sheriff. \n|LineColor=195905\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber2=29\n|EpisodeNumber=105\n|Title=The Double\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1958|3|22|df=y}}\n|WrittenBy=Basil Dawson\n|DirectedBy=Gerry Bryant\n|ShortSummary=SUMMARY: Prince John has ordered the Sheriff to Kill Prince Arthur, and Bolbec ([[John Gabriel (actor)|John Gabriel]]), has found a double, Luke Tanner, for Robin Hood and the sheriff hatches a plan for the double to kill the Prince. When Lady Constance ([[Pamela Alan]]), Prince Arthur ([[Richard O'Sullivan]]) and their Emissary ([[Richard Thorp]]) arrive in Sherwood and meet Robin Hood who knows of the plans from Friar Tuck and has to save the Prince and Luke Tanner. \n|LineColor=195905\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber2=30\n|EpisodeNumber=106\n|Title=At the Sign of the Blue Boar\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1958|3|23|df=y}}\n|WrittenBy=Sidney B. Wells\n|DirectedBy=Ernest Bornemann\n|ShortSummary=OPENING SCENE CHORUS (Merry men singing at Blue Boar Inn): \"Thar 'hue and cry' rang out my lads! They trailed us to the glen, the glen! The Sheriff's breath was lost my lads, on Sherwood's merry men! From out the noose we slithered loose his lordship fooled again, again! Thar 'hue and cry' rang out my lads! They trailed us to the glen, the glen! The Sheriff's breath was lost my lads, on Sherwood's merry men! So sing and send a cheery note bring out your billed and then and then, the Sheriff will n'er be called mein host, by Sherwood's Merry Men!\"<br />SUMMARY: When a Tailor, Master William Blount ([[Geoffrey Chater]]) covets the ownership of the Blue Boar 